nl: Suppose that $f$ is holomorphic in an open set $\Omega$. Prove that if $\text{Re}(f)$ is constant, then $f$ is constant.
lean:
∀ {f : ℂ → ℂ} (Ω : Set ℂ) (a b : Ω) (h : IsOpen Ω)
  (hf : DifferentiableOn ℂ f Ω) (hc : ∃ (c : ℝ), ∀ z ∈ Ω, (f z).re = c), f a = f b
candidate: ∀ {Ω : Set ℂ} (f : ℂ → ℂ) (hf : IsOpen Ω) (hf_holo : ∀ z ∈ Ω, DifferentiableAt ℂ f z) (h_re_const : ∃ c : ℝ, ∀ z ∈ Ω, (f z).re = c) : ∃ c, ℂ, ∀ z ∈ Ω, f z = c
imports:
import Mathlib

open Complex Filter Function Metric Finset
open scoped BigOperators Topology
